"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.4.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.4.2</span> Net</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">חֵרֶם</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(cherem)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:26\">ECC 7:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:2\">MIC 7:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מִכְמָר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(mikmar)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:20\">ISA 51:20</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מָצוֹד</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(matsod (see )</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:26\">ECC 7:26</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מְצוּדָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(mtsudah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:11\">PSA 66:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:13\">EZK 12:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:20\">EZK 17:20</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">רֶשֶׁת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(resheth)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job18:8\">JOB 18:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:16\">PSA 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:9\">PSA 10:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:15\">PSA 25:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:5\">PSA 31:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:7\">PSA 35:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:8\">PSA 35:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:7\">PSA 57:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps140:6\">PSA 140:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:17\">PRO 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:5\">PRO 29:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:13\">LAM 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:13\">EZK 12:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:20\">EZK 17:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:8\">EZK 19:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:1\">HOS 5:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:12\">HOS 7:12</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">παγίς</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pagis)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:35\">LUK 21:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:9\">ROM 11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:7\">1TI 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:9\">1TI 6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:26\">2TI 2:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob14:10\">TOB 14:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob14:10\">TOB 14:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis14:11\">WIS 14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir9:3\">SIR 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir9:13\">SIR 9:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir27:20\">SIR 27:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir27:26\">SIR 27:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir27:29\">SIR 27:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir51:2\">SIR 51:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc1:35\">1MA 1:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc5:4\">1MA 5:4</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0339_hunting_net.jpg\" alt=\"Men trapping deer in a net (Relief from the lion hunt of king Ashurbanipal, Northern Palace, Nineveh, Room S, panels 17-18, c. 645-635 BCE)\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Men trapping deer in a net (Relief from the lion hunt of king Ashurbanipal, Northern Palace, Nineveh, Room S, panels 17–18, c. 645–635 BCE) (© Zunkir, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>The net was a mesh or very loose fabric made of string.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The net was a hunting tool. It was put in places where a bird or animal might fly or run into it and become entangled. Nets could also be used actively in hunting, that is, the hunter stalked the prey, and when he got close enough, he threw the net over his quarry.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Since snares or traps for capturing birds or animals are almost universal, there should be no difficulty involved in obtaining an appropriate term. In many contexts, however, it cannot be certain if the net spoken of is for hunting animals or for hunting birds. In languages where no distinction is required, a generic term for “net” may be used. Where a distinction must be made, the context should be checked carefully. The following breakdown indicates which passages refer to nets for animals (including human beings), which ones refer to nets for birds, and which ones are unclear:</p>\n<p>Animals: <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:16\">PSA 9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:7\">PSA 35:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:8\">PSA 35:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:5\">PRO 29:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:20\">ISA 51:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:13\">LAM 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:13\">EZK 12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:20\">EZK 17:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:8\">EZK 19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:7\">1TI 3:7</a>; [<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir9:13\">SIR 9:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir27:20\">SIR 27:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir27:26\">SIR 27:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir27:29\">SIR 27:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc1:35\">1MA 1:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc5:4\">1MA 5:4</a> ]</p>\n<p>Birds: <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:17\">PRO 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:12\">HOS 7:12</a></p>\n<p>Unclear: <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job18:8\">JOB 18:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:9\">PSA 10:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:15\">PSA 25:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:5\">PSA 31:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:7\">PSA 57:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps140:6\">PSA 140:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:26\">ECC 7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:1\">HOS 5:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:35\">LUK 21:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:9\">ROM 11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:9\">1TI 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:26\">2TI 2:26</a>; [<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob14:10\">TOB 14:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis14:11\">WIS 14:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir9:3\">SIR 9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir51:2\">SIR 51:2</a> ]</p>\n<p>In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:35\">LUK 21:35</a> it is not so much the physical object that is in focus but rather the unexpected nature of the event; however, the object is usually retained in translation.</p>\n<p>In cases where the text is speaking figuratively, it may be possible to avoid using the figure of a net, especially where such a reference would be misleading; for example, in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:2\">MIC 7:2</a> d <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> says “everyone is trying to trap someone else.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
